all"],"type":"node"}," ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["ϕ_m(tA)b"],"type":"node"}," products up to order ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["k"],"type":"node"}," is returned as a matrix. This is because it's more economical to produce all the results at once than individually. A second output is returned if ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["errest=true"],"type":"node"}," in ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["kwargs"],"type":"node"},". The error estimate is given for the second-to-last product, using the last product as an estimator. If ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["correct=true"],"type":"node"},", then ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["ϕ_0"],"type":"node"}," through ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["ϕ_(k-1)"],"type":"node"}," are updated using the last Arnoldi vector. The correction algorithm is described in [1]."],"type":"node"},{"attributes":{},"tag":"p","children":["You can adjust how the Krylov subspace is constructed by setting various keyword arguments. See the Arnoldi iteration section for more details."],"type":"node"},{"attributes":{},"tag":"h2","children":["Contributing"],"type":"node"},{"attributes":{},"tag":"ul","children":[{"attributes":{},"tag":"li","children":[{"attributes":{},"tag":"p","children":["Please refer to the ",{"attributes":{"href":"https://github.com/SciML/ColPrac/blob/master/README.md","title":""},"tag":"a","children":["SciML ColPrac: Contributor's Guide on Collaborative Practices for Community Packages"],"type":"node"}," for guidance on PRs, issues, and other matters relating to contributing to ModelingToolkit."],"type":"node"}],"type":"node"},{"attributes":{},"tag":"li","children":[{"attributes":{},"tag":"p","children":["There are a few community forums:"],"type":"node"},{"attributes":{},"tag":"ul","children":[{"attributes":{},"tag":"li","children":[{"attributes":{},"tag":"p","children":["the #diffeq-bridged channel in the ",{"attributes":{"href":"https://jul